Quote:   Drinking on the West Coast has an etiquette of its own. It condones none of the `bob-in' touch of a city bar when the man will have the two drinks he wants and then leave. `Be in or be out', you will be told, is the motto on the Coast.
Notes:  (Pascoe `Coal from Buller')
